section.section:
An organization that meets the conditions of paragraph (2) of this subsection may conduct a gaming event for the benefit of any of the following listed organizations if the organization is a bona fide:
religious organization;
fraternal organization;
civic organization;
veterans' hospital;
amateur athletic organization in which all playing members are under the age of 18 years; or
charitable organization.

An organization conducting a gaming event shall:
be located in Baltimore City; and
spend a majority of the organization's funds in Baltimore City for:
fraternal purposes;
civic purposes;
purposes related to a veterans' hospital;
purposes related to amateur athletics; or
charitable purposes.
